<title>USA: Mikros Systems names DiPiano president. [CORRECTED 14:55 GMT]</title>
<headline>Mikros Systems names DiPiano president. [CORRECTED 14:55 GMT]</headline>
<dateline>PRINCETON, N.J. 1997-04-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Mikros Systems Corp said on Friday it had named Michael DiPiano (corrects spelling), formerly of Safeguard Scientifics Inc, president overseeing day-to-day operations.</p>
<p>In November 1996, Safeguard bought common shares amounting to 10 percent of Mikros' common stock on a fully diluted basis for $1 million.  Under the terms of the pact, Safeguard has the option to increase its holdings by an additional 20 percent.  </p>
<p>DiPiano takes over the position of president from Thomas Meaney, who continues as chief executive, a spokeswoman for Mikros said.</p>
